<main id="main" class="wrap">

  <!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">A jonnify course</p>
    <h1>Functional Programming<br>in <span class="ex">Elixir</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">A bridge from the algebra you already know to real-time systems on the BEAM.</p>
    <p class="kicker">Six chapters, 54 modules, plus an optional history chapter. Every idea is
      defined precisely, paired with its Elixir form, and shown — not only described. The code is idiomatic
      and runnable; the diagrams compute the real thing.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra"}>Begin &nbsp;·&nbsp; F1 Algebra <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/course"}>Course contents</a>
    </div>

    <svg class="hero-motif" viewBox="0 0 1000 96" role="img" aria-label="A pipeline: lambda, compose, pipe.">
      <line x1="40" y1="48" x2="960" y2="48" class="arc-flow"></line>
      <g fill="none" stroke="#d4a85a" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.85">
        <circle cx="190" cy="48" r="26"></circle>
        <circle cx="500" cy="48" r="26"></circle>
        <circle cx="810" cy="48" r="26"></circle>
      </g>
      <g font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="22" fill="#cdb8f0" text-anchor="middle" opacity="0.92">
        <text x="190" y="56">&#955;</text>
        <text x="500" y="56">&#8728;</text>
        <text x="810" y="55">|&gt;</text>
      </g>
      <g fill="#a39c89" opacity="0.8">
        <path d="M330 42 l12 6 l-12 6 z"></path>
        <path d="M640 42 l12 6 l-12 6 z"></path>
      </g>
    </svg>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== HOW TO READ ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>How to read this</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This course makes one claim and then earns it: functional programming is the algebra of
        functions, and Elixir is a place to run that algebra at scale. Each chapter takes an idea you
        already trust from mathematics and shows the line that connects it to working code.</p>
      <p>The shape is deliberate. <strong>Algebra</strong> establishes the mindset; <strong>functional
        programming</strong> studies the tools on their own terms; the <strong>Elixir language</strong>
        gives them a syntax; <strong>algorithms</strong> put them under load; <strong>pragmatic
        engineering</strong> ships them; and <strong>Phoenix</strong> carries them onto the web and into
        real-time. Each chapter reuses the one before it, so nothing arrives without its foundation.</p>
      <p>Pick a chapter from the arc below to see what it covers and what it stands on. The full module
        directory follows.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- INTERACTIVE 1 — the arc -->
    <figure class="fig" aria-labelledby="arcTitle">
      <h4 id="arcTitle" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:.8rem;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--cream-dim);margin:0 0 1rem">The arc · select a chapter</h4>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1000 152" role="group" aria-label="The six chapters as a single arc. Select one for detail.">
        <line x1="90" y1="62" x2="932" y2="62" class="arc-flow"></line>
        <g class="arc-arrow"><path d="M164 56 l13 6 l-13 6 z"></path></g>
        <g class="arc-arrow"><path d="M324 56 l13 6 l-13 6 z"></path></g>
        <g class="arc-arrow"><path d="M484 56 l13 6 l-13 6 z"></path></g>
        <g class="arc-arrow"><path d="M644 56 l13 6 l-13 6 z"></path></g>
        <g class="arc-arrow"><path d="M804 56 l13 6 l-13 6 z"></path></g>

        <g class="arc-node active" data-ch="F1" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F1, Algebra">
          <rect x="24" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="90" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">1</text>
          <text class="nm" x="90" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Algebra</text>
        </g>
        <g class="arc-node" data-ch="F2" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F2, Functional Programming">
          <rect x="184" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="250" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">2</text>
          <text class="nm" x="250" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Functional</text>
        </g>
        <g class="arc-node" data-ch="F3" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F3, The Elixir Language">
          <rect x="344" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="410" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">3</text>
          <text class="nm" x="410" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Language</text>
        </g>
        <g class="arc-node" data-ch="F4" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F4, Algorithms and Data Structures">
          <rect x="504" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="570" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">4</text>
          <text class="nm" x="570" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Algorithms</text>
        </g>
        <g class="arc-node" data-ch="F5" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F5, Pragmatic Programming">
          <rect x="664" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="730" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">5</text>
          <text class="nm" x="730" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Pragmatic</text>
        </g>
        <g class="arc-node" data-ch="F6" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Chapter F6, Phoenix Framework">
          <rect x="824" y="22" width="132" height="80" rx="16" fill="#10162b" stroke="#2a3252"></rect>
          <text class="num" x="890" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="30">6</text>
          <text class="nm" x="890" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Phoenix</text>
        </g>

        <text x="90" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#7ba387">start</text>
        <text x="890" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="11" fill="#9fc0ea">real-time</text>
      </svg>

      <div class="arc-readout">
        <div class="nm" id="arcNm">Algebra</div>
        <p class="one" id="arcOne">The functional mindset, straight from the math you already know.</p>
        <div class="meta">
          <span><b id="arcId">F1</b> &middot; chapter</span>
          <span><b id="arcMods">9</b> modules</span>
          <span id="arcReuse">Starts from the algebra you already know.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arc-open" id="arcOpen"><a href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra"}>Open F1 &middot; Algebra <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></div>
      </div>
    </figure>
    <p class="take">The course is one curve, not eight disconnected topics. Read it in order and each chapter
      is a consequence of the last.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== THE PIPE ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>One idea, early: composition</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The thread that runs through every chapter is composition. In algebra, applying <span class="math">f</span>
        and then <span class="math">g</span> is the single function <span class="math">g&#8728;f</span>. In Elixir, that
        same act has a syntax — the pipe <code class="inl">|&gt;</code> — which reads left to right in the order the
        work happens.</p>
      <p>Three pure functions are wired below: <strong>double</strong> maps <span class="math">x</span> to
        <span class="math">2x</span>, <strong>increment</strong> adds one, and <strong>square</strong> maps
        <span class="math">x</span> to <span class="math">x&#178;</span>. Set the input, toggle which functions take
        part, and watch the pipeline and its result rebuild.</p>
    </div>

    <figure class="fig" aria-labelledby="pipeTitle">
      <h4 id="pipeTitle" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:.8rem;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--cream-dim);margin:0 0 1rem">The pipe · build a pipeline</h4>
      <div class="controls">
        <div class="fold-ctrl">
          <label for="pipeX">input&nbsp;x</label>
          <input type="range" id="pipeX" min="0" max="12" step="1" value="3">
          <span class="val" id="pipeXval">3</span>
        </div>
        <div class="solid-select" id="pipeStages" role="group" aria-label="Functions in the pipeline">
          <button type="button" data-stage="double" data-c="blue" class="active" aria-pressed="true">double</button>
          <button type="button" data-stage="inc" data-c="sage" class="active" aria-pressed="true">increment</button>
          <button type="button" data-stage="square" data-c="gold" class="active" aria-pressed="true">square</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <pre class="code" id="pipeCode" aria-live="polite"><span class="res">3</span>
<span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn blue">double</span>()    <span class="cmt"># =&gt; 6</span>
<span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn sage">increment</span>() <span class="cmt"># =&gt; 7</span>
<span class="op">|&gt;</span> <span class="fn gold">square</span>()    <span class="cmt"># =&gt; 49</span></pre>

      <div class="geo-readout" id="pipeChain" aria-live="polite">3 &#9655; 6 &#9655; 7 &#9655; 49 <span class="dim">&nbsp;=&nbsp;49</span></div>
    </figure>
    <p class="take">A pipeline reads left to right: <code class="inl">x |&gt; f |&gt; g</code> is
      <span class="math">g(f(x))</span>. Turn every function off and the pipeline is the identity — it returns its
      input untouched. F1.03 makes <span class="math">f&#8728;g</span> and its associativity precise.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== THE MAP ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>The map</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The full course, chapter by chapter. Cards that link are ready to read; the rest are specified and on
        the way. The <span class="math">.09</span> of every chapter is a hands-on, richly visual lab.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="legend">
      <span><span class="pill live">live</span> chapter front door</span>
      <span><span class="pill built">built</span> lesson ready</span>
      <span><span class="pill planned">planned</span> drafted, on the way</span>
      <span><span class="pill soon">soon</span> specified</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F0</span><h3>History</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/course"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Where this came from — the languages, the runtimes, and the BEAM.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/course/fp-evolution"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F0.1</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The evolution of functional languages &amp; runtimes</p><p class="o">λ-calculus → LISP → ML/Haskell → the immutable turn.</p><ul class="dives"><li><span class="dn">F0.1.1</span><span>From λ-calculus to LISP</span></li><li><span class="dn">F0.1.2</span><span>Types &amp; laziness — the ML and Haskell branch</span></li><li><span class="dn">F0.1.3</span><span>The immutable turn — persistent data on the JVM &amp; CLR</span></li></ul></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/course/beam-evolution"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F0.2</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The evolution of Erlang, the BEAM &amp; OTP</p><p class="o">Telecom roots, soft-real-time scheduling, and supervision.</p><ul class="dives"><li><span class="dn">F0.2.1</span><span>Telecom roots &amp; “let it crash”</span></li><li><span class="dn">F0.2.2</span><span>Inside the BEAM — scheduling, heaps &amp; soft-real-time GC</span></li><li><span class="dn">F0.2.3</span><span>OTP &amp; the supervision tree — and the polyglot BEAM</span></li></ul></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F1</span><h3>Algebra</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">The functional mindset, straight from the math you already know.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/functions"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">What a function really is</p><p class="o">Mapping, domain &amp; range, exactly one output → first-class functions.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/substitution"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The substitution model</p><p class="o">Equals for equals → referential transparency and purity.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/composition"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Composition, f∘g</p><p class="o">Chaining mappings, associativity → the pipe.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/immutability"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Immutability &amp; binding</p><p class="o">A symbol names a fixed value → immutable data.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/collections"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Sets, sequences &amp; mappings</p><p class="o">Applying f across a collection → lists, maps, Enum.map.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/recursion"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Recursion &amp; induction</p><p class="o">Base case + step, and the proof → recursion, no loops.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/higher-order"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Higher-order operators (Σ, Π)</p><p class="o">Operators over functions → map / filter / reduce.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/pattern-matching"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Equations &amp; pattern matching</p><p class="o">Identities, solving by structure → pattern matching.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algebra/plotting-lab"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F1.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Functions on the plane — a plotting lab</p><p class="o">Plot and compose functions; watch f∘g as curves.</p></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F2</span><h3>Functional Programming</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Pure functions, immutability, and higher-order functions on their own terms.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/pure"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Pure functions &amp; side effects</p><p class="o">What purity buys; isolating effects.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/persistence"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Immutability &amp; persistent data</p><p class="o">Structural sharing; why copying is cheap.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/higher-order"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Higher-order functions</p><p class="o">Functions as arguments and return values.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/recursion"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Recursion patterns &amp; tail calls</p><p class="o">Accumulators and tail-call optimisation.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/folds"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">map / filter / reduce (folds)</p><p class="o">reduce as the universal fold.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/closures"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Closures &amp; partial application</p><p class="o">Capturing environment; &amp; and currying by hand.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/adt"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Algebraic data types</p><p class="o">Sum and product types; tagged tuples.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/composition"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Composition &amp; pipelines</p><p class="o">Building programs by composing functions.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/functional/pipeline-lab"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F2.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The data-pipeline lab</p><p class="o">Compose map/filter/reduce over a dataset; watch each stage.</p></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F3</span><h3>The Elixir Language</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Syntax, pipelines, pattern matching, and structs on the BEAM.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/values"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Values, types &amp; IEx</p><p class="o">The data you build with; the shell as a tool.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/match"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Pattern matching &amp; the match operator</p><p class="o">= is a match, not assignment.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/modules"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Functions, modules &amp; the pipe</p><p class="o">Defining and composing in modules.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/enum-streams"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Enumerables &amp; streams</p><p class="o">Eager versus lazy traversal.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/structs"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Structs, maps &amp; keyword lists</p><p class="o">Shaping data; when to use which.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/protocols"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Protocols &amp; behaviours</p><p class="o">Polymorphism and contracts.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/processes"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Processes &amp; the actor model</p><p class="o">spawn, send, receive; isolation.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/otp"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">OTP: GenServer &amp; supervisors</p><p class="o">Stateful servers and fault tolerance.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/language/playground"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F3.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The process playground</p><p class="o">Spawn processes, send messages, watch the mailbox live.</p></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F4</span><h3>Algorithms &amp; Data Structures</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Classical and advanced problems, from lists to branded CHAMP tries.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/lists"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Lists, recursion &amp; complexity</p><p class="o">Cons cells; big-O on the BEAM.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/trees"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Trees &amp; traversals</p><p class="o">Binary and n-ary trees; DFS/BFS, functionally.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/sorting"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Sorting &amp; searching</p><p class="o">Merge/quick sort and binary search, immutably.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/maps"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Maps, sets &amp; hashing</p><p class="o">Hash maps, collisions, the cost model.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/hamt"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Hash Array Mapped Tries (HAMT)</p><p class="o">Persistent maps via prefix trees.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/champ"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">CHAMP maps</p><p class="o">Compressed Hash-Array Mapped Prefix-trees; layout &amp; iteration.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/identifiers"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Identifiers, Snowflake &amp; branded ids</p><p class="o">From naive ids to a Snowflake bigint and a branded, base62 id.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/persistence"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Branded ids &amp; persistence</p><p class="o">Branded ids as keys in SQLite, PostgreSQL, and Redis.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/branded-champ"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Branded CHAMP maps &amp; GenServer</p><p class="o">A CHAMP keyed by branded ids, partitioned by namespace, behind a GenServer.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/recipes"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.10</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Practical recipes in Elixir</p><p class="o">Turning algorithmic problems into idiomatic Elixir.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/dynamic-programming"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.11</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Dynamic programming &amp; advanced problems</p><p class="o">Overlapping subproblems, memoized and tabulated.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/algorithms/lab"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F4.12</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Lab: build a branded CHAMP store</p><p class="o">An interactive lab: insert branded keys and watch the partitioned CHAMP restructure.</p></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F5</span><h3>Pragmatic Programming</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Real-world engineering: structure, testing, telemetry, releases.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/foundations"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Foundations</p><p class="o">Start thin: a running Portal from day one.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/domain"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Modeling the Portal domain</p><p class="o">Bounded contexts, structs, and the public API.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/tracer-bullets"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Tracer bullets: a walking skeleton</p><p class="o">Thin end-to-end first, then iterate.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/contracts"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Design by contract</p><p class="o">Preconditions, postconditions, and failing fast.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/cqrs"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Commands, queries &amp; events</p><p class="o">Separate writes from reads; the engine as a reducer over events.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/state"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Where engine state lives</p><p class="o">One process holds the state; one supervisor keeps it alive.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/testing"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Pragmatic testing</p><p class="o">Testing the pure core, property-based tests, and contracts as tests.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/boundaries"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Boundaries &amp; integration seams</p><p class="o">Ports out, a facade in, one error vocabulary for the UI.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/pragmatic/engine-lab"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F5.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Lab: the Portal engine, LiveView-ready</p><p class="o">Assemble the engine end to end, then mount it behind a LiveView.</p></a></div></section>
<section class="chap reveal"><div class="chap-head"><span class="cid">F6</span><h3>Phoenix Framework</h3><a class="chap-link" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix"}>Open chapter →</a><p class="c-one">Web applications on Elixir, and the road into real-time LiveView.</p></div><div class="mods"><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/lifecycle"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.01</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Architecture &amp; the request lifecycle</p><p class="o">endpoint → router → controller → view.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/routing"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.02</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Routing, controllers &amp; plugs</p><p class="o">The plug pipeline.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/ecto"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.03</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Ecto: schemas, changesets &amp; queries</p><p class="o">Data, validation, the repo.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/contexts"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.04</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Contexts &amp; domain design</p><p class="o">Boundaries that scale.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/heex"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.05</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Templates, components &amp; HEEx</p><p class="o">Server-rendered markup.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/liveview"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.06</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Phoenix LiveView fundamentals</p><p class="o">Interactive UIs without hand-written JS.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/pubsub"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.07</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">PubSub, channels &amp; real-time</p><p class="o">Live updates over WebSockets.</p></a><a class="mod" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/deployment"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.08</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">Auth, deployment &amp; going live</p><p class="o">Sessions, releases, production.</p></a><a class="mod lab" href={PortalWeb.deep_link_base() <> "/elixir/phoenix/live-dashboard"}><div class="top"><span class="num">F6.09</span><span class="pill built">built</span></div><p class="t">The live dashboard</p><p class="o">Real-time LiveView state over a socket; multi-client via PubSub.</p></a></div></section>

